    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Boil a kettle</p><p>Cut your <strong>waxy potatoes</strong> (skin on) into large bite-sized pieces</p><p>Add the <strong>chopped potatoes</strong> to a pot of <strong>boiled water</strong> with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong>, bring to the boil over a high heat and cook for 12-15 min or until fork-tender</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/crispy-basa-with-dill-sauce/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, rip the leaves off your <strong>spring greens</strong>, discard the tough stalks, then layer the leaves over each other, roll them up & slice into thin strips</p><p>Tear your <strong>white cup mushrooms</strong> into bite-sized pieces (this saves time and creates an interesting texture)</p><p>Chop your <strong>dill </strong>finely, including the stalks</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/crispy-basa-with-dill-sauce/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Combine 3 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[4 1/2 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[6 tbsp]</span> <strong>flour</strong> with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong> on a large plate</p><p>Pat your <strong>basa fillet[s]</strong> dry with kitchen paper</p><p>Transfer the <strong>basa</strong> to the<strong> seasoned flour</strong> and pat until evenly coated, shaking off any excess</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/crispy-basa-with-dill-sauce/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once the pan is hot, add the <strong>floured basa</strong> and cook for 3-4 min on each side</p><p>Once cooked, remove the pan from the heat and set aside until serving</p><p>Tip: Your fish is cooked when it turns opaque and flakes easily</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/crispy-basa-with-dill-sauce/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the potatoes are tender, add the <strong>sliced spring greens</strong> and cook for 2-3 min further</p><p>Drain the <strong>potatoes & spring greens</strong>, drizzle with <strong>olive oil</strong> and season with <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong></p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/crispy-basa-with-dill-sauce/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a large knob of <strong>butter</strong> over a medium heat</p><p>Once hot, add the<strong> mushrooms</strong> and cook for 2-3 min or until starting to crisp</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/crispy-basa-with-dill-sauce/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the mushrooms are crisped, add your <strong>stock mix</strong>, <strong>white wine vinegar</strong>, <strong>clotted cream</strong> and 150ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[200ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[250ml]</span> <strong>milk</strong> to the pan, then cook for 2 min or until the sauce is slightly thickened</p><p>Add the <strong>chopped dill</strong> and season with a generous grind of <strong>black pepper</strong> \u2013 this is your <strong>sauce bonne femme</strong></p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/crispy-basa-with-dill-sauce/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the<strong> basa</strong> over the <strong>sauce</strong> <strong>bonne femme</strong> with the <strong>potatoes</strong> <strong>& spring greens</strong> to the side</p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
